    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Campodeidae (Hexapoda: Diplura) from Kyrgyzstan, Central Asia, with the description of a remarkable new genus and species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761393>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761399>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761395>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761397>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761401>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761403>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761405> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761393>
    dc:description "Figs 2−9. Ak-Turpak Cave, Kadamjay District, Batken Region in Kyrgyzstan in CentralAsia.2. Whitish, pinkish, or reddish clayey ground surface where the entrance is located. 3. Entrance of the cave, exterior view. 4. Entrance of the cave, interior view. 5. Small platforms and mattresses near the entrance. 6. Stairs installed deep inside the cave. 7. Last chamber of the cave, which is always associated with old bat guano.8. Individual of Kyrgyzstancampa sanare Sendra & Ferreira gen. et sp. nov., observed amidst guano. 9. Another specimen of K. sanare Sendra & Ferreira gen. et sp. nov." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5761393/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761399>
    dc:description "Figs 16−18. Kyrgyzstancampa sanare Sendra & Ferreira gen. et sp. nov. 16. ♂, paratype (Coll. AS), detail of mesonotum. 17. ♂, paratype (Coll. AS), detail of lateral posterior mesonotum. 18. ♀, holotype (IBB 92101), thoracic nota." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5761399/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761395>
    dc:description "Figs 10−12. Kyrgyzstancampa sanare Sendra & Ferreira gen. et sp. nov., ♂, paratype (Coll. AS). 10. Cupuliform organ in the last antennomere. 11. Medial antennomere. 12. Gouge sensillum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5761395/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761397>
    dc:description "Figs 13−15. Kyrgyzstancampa sanare Sendra & Ferreira gen. et sp. nov. 13. ♂, paratype (Coll. AS), 3rd antennomere. 14. ♂, paratype (Coll. AS), sensillum of 3rd antennomere. 15. ♀, holotype (IBB 92101), left portion of the head at dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5761397/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761401>
    dc:description "Figs 19−24. Kyrgyzstancampa sanare Sendra & Ferreira gen. et sp. nov., ♂, paratype (Coll. AS). 19. Lateral view of end portion of metathorax and first and second abdominal segments with methatoracic legs. 20. Large, deep joint between femur and tibia with a longitudinal protrusion on the inner side in a metathoracic leg. 21. Lateral view of pretarsus in metathoracic leg. 22. Lateral view of pretarsus in metathoracic leg, here they observed the ventral spines on the claws. 23. Dorsal view of pretarsus in metathoracic leg. 24. Detail of lateral processes on pretarsus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5761401/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761403>
    dc:description "Figs 25−26. Kyrgyzstancampa sanare Sendra & Ferreira gen. et sp. nov., urosternite I, lateral side.25. ♂, paratype (MZB (MCNB) 2021-2339). 26. ♀, paratype (MZB (MCNB) 2021-2338). Abbreviations: a 1 = glandular setae in distal portion of appendages; a 2 = lateral-ventral glandular setae; g 1 = posterior glandular setae of urosternite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5761403/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5761405>
    dc:description "Figs 27−28. Turkmenocampa edaphica Sendra & Sánchez-García sp., ♂, paratype (Coll. AS). 27. Cupuliform organ in the last antennomere. 28. Medial antennomere with gouge sensilla." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5761405/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

